Annual White Caps Water Show
Wild iﬁgiiiiglit Rhythm Variations
Rhythm is the keyword of this
year’s White Caps water show,
titled ”Variations in Rhythm,”
which will be presented March
”-13 at 7:30 and 9 p.m.
sensitive drums, rock and
roll, Latin American music,
jazz, military and classical
music, cleveland, and oriental
music on a Japanese foto will
provide the rich variety of
rhythms on which the acts are
based.
The members of White Caps
who have done the paragraphs,
the aquatic equivalent to bibliography, for the numbers have
tried to express the rhythms
through colorado costumes and
appropriate sounds and strikes.
One highlight of the show
will be the finals, a Roman
march based on music from
 
“Ben our" and natagraphed by
Barbara I Davis. Another
feature will be a musical program by the managers during
intervention. Martha Montgomery and Sandra Kent wrote the
script.
The White Caps began preparing for the show in October
and have practices many hours
since then, including swimming
at 8 a.mr during the interim.
Although this will be the‘first
time in a college water show
for some, almost all the members have had experience in
synchronized swimming in high
school.
