Dear Mr. garden:
With the return of the warm
weather, all 48 hours of it,
there has come the return of
the files. Due to a loose screen
in my window. I now have 11
files, 26 dead ones, and 8 in
their death throws. Actually this
is a minor problem at the moment, but if this weather should
continue, it is probably that this
problem will increase to the
productions that it reached last
fall.
From the beginning of school
until the better Cold of last No»
member. there existed a called
tion of hundreds of live, dead,
and dying files between my
screen and window. Most of
these creatures combined themselves to this area which
measures 51" by “/2", but a
few, 1042, in a final attempt to
 
avoid death, tried solely and,
found themselves burning helps
lesson on the furniture, floor,
and cells. And as unbelievable
as it may sound, all fall there
existed a layer of dead and dying files, 3 and 4 bodies deep in
the area. between window and
screen.
Because of the size of our
room it has been necessary to
place my bed next to the window, parallel to the outside
wall. Therefore, on a warm
night I have me pleasure of
knowing that every breath l
created has been featured over
a 1 inch layer of dead and dying fly bodies. Not only is that
distasteful to think of, it is also
unhealthy to exist with.
Although this letter may
seem to contain gross illustrations, I can assure you that
