By Karen robinson
paths Yoga is Grinnell's new—
est way of physical condition
ing.
The Yoga Club, organized
and taught by Phil Brown, offers an alternative to Body
Building with the Royal radar
dean Air Force program. Work
in this club may count as a
_ minor in physical education.
paths Yoga is an exercise
program based upon deep
breathing while maintaining
various pictures. Its history
reaches back over 2000 years
and its foundation lies in the
philosophical systems of the
East.
“Yoga, in its Indian context,
is a set of six philosophical
systems whose interests seek
Spiritual union with the transcendant self,” said Phil.
He explained, “Each person
may choose the yoga he finds
best. paths Yoga is a part of
Raja Yoga, the most sophisticated system which is based
upon concentration and meditation. Concentration requires.
a strong, healthy, pure mind,
and this in turn requires a
strong, healthy, and pure
body. This is where paths
Yoga comes in. It is the yoga
of physical conditioning.
“Although paths Yoga is
‘ part of a way of life, the exercises are good in themselves.
I’m not really teaching Yoga,
but merely the Yoga system of
exercise.”
In this program the perception of all systems of the body
is arrested. circular development is only one of a number
